 # Types of Network Attacks and Defensive Measures

## 1. What Are Network Attacks?
Actions taken by malicious actors to disrupt, damage, or gain unauthorized access to networks and systems.

## 2. Types of Network Attacks
A. Passive Attacks

Eavesdropping: Intercepting data in transit.
Example: Man-in-the-middle (MITM) attacks.
B. Active Attacks

Denial of Service (DoS): Overwhelming a server with traffic to make it unavailable.
Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS): Same as DoS but using multiple systems.
C. Insider Threats

Malicious or negligent actions by authorized users.
Example: Employee stealing sensitive data.
D. Phishing

Sending fake emails or messages to trick users into revealing credentials.
E. Spoofing

Pretending to be a trusted device or user.
Examples: IP spoofing or email spoofing.
F. Malware Attacks

Infecting systems with malicious software.
Types: Viruses, worms, ransomware, spyware.
